euai_c:1976fa863c3bd756b8770eed1e8ade6ca93ec2a8 a euai:DocumentChunk ;
    euai:chunkOf <https://euaiact.eu/resource/Document/EUAIAct-1-44_pdf> ;
    euai:chunkText " the relevant procedural requirements set by the Regulation (EC) No 810/2009 of the European Parliament and  OJ L, 12.7.2024 EN ELI: http://data.europa.eu/eli/reg/2024/1689/oj 17/144" ;
    euai:contentOffset 118850 ;
    euai:fileName "EUAIAct-1-44.pdf" ;
    euai:pageNumber 17 ;
    euai:position 245 .

euai_c:2cfe5a45bfc0d19c26cfa4a30c1be120a231d23f a euai:DocumentChunk ;
    euai:chunkOf <https://euaiact.eu/resource/Document/EUAIAct-1-44_pdf> ;
    euai:chunkText ".eu/eli/reg/2024/1689/oj 39/144 (46) Regulation (EU) No 575/2013 of the European Parliament and of the Council of 26 June 2013 on prudential requirements for credit  institutions and investment firms and amending Regulation (EU) No 648/2012 (OJ L 176, 27.6.2013, p. 1). (47) Directive 2008/48/EC of the European Parliament and of the Council of 23 April" ;
    euai:contentOffset 273428 ;
    euai:fileName "EUAIAct-1-44.pdf" ;
    euai:pageNumber 39 ;
    euai:position 548 .

euai_c:34c32e8325cb20255e9823bf47982cfc4b83e83a a euai:DocumentChunk ;
    euai:chunkOf <https://euaiact.eu/resource/Document/EUAIAct-1-44_pdf> ;
    euai:chunkText "EC and  2002/65/EC of the European Parliament and of the Council and Regulation (EC) No 2006/2004 of the European Parliament and of  the Council (‘Unfair Commercial Practices Directive’) (OJ L 149, 11.6.2005, p. 22)." ;
    euai:contentOffset 62280 ;
    euai:fileName "EUAIAct-1-44.pdf" ;
    euai:pageNumber 9 ;
    euai:position 128 .

euai_c:3ee390c44518d85d10cb71af115599af5bff7322 a euai:DocumentChunk ;
    euai:chunkOf <https://euaiact.eu/resource/Document/EUAIAct-1-44_pdf> ;
    euai:chunkText "1139 and (EU) 2019/2144 and  Directives 2014/90/EU, (EU) 2016/797 and (EU) 2020/1828 (Artificial Intelligence Act) (Text with EEA relevance) THE EUROPEAN PARLIAMENT AND THE COUNCIL OF THE EUROPEAN UNION, Having regard to the Treaty on the Functioning of the European Union, and in particular Articles 16 and 114 thereof, Having regard to the proposal from the European" ;
    euai:contentOffset 300 ;
    euai:fileName "EUAIAct-1-44.pdf" ;
    euai:pageNumber 1 ;
    euai:position 2 .

euai_c:7c0263683362fba0955bb649d91de984454db924 a euai:DocumentChunk ;
    euai:chunkOf <https://euaiact.eu/resource/Document/EUAIAct-1-44_pdf> ;
    euai:chunkText "(27) While the risk-based approach is the basis for a proportionate and effective set of binding rules, it is important to  recall the 2019 Ethics guidelines for trustworthy AI developed by the independent AI HLEG appointed by the  Commission. In those guidelines, the AI HLEG developed seven non-binding ethical principles for AI which are  intended to help ensure that AI is trustworthy and ethically sound. The seven principles include human agency and  oversight; technical robustness and safety;" ;
    euai:contentOffset 47997 ;
    euai:fileName "EUAIAct-1-44.pdf" ;
    euai:pageNumber 8 ;
    euai:position 100 .

euai_c:abbe116671d427e63961f7d37a04a2467de53246 a euai:DocumentChunk ;
    euai:chunkOf <https://euaiact.eu/resource/Document/EUAIAct-1-44_pdf> ;
    euai:chunkText " for the implementation of the relevant obligations, if, by the time this Regulation becomes applicable,  a code of practice cannot be finalised or is not deemed adequate by the AI Office. Once a harmonised standard is  EN OJ L, 12.7.2024 30/144 ELI: http://data.europa.eu/eli/reg/2024/1689/oj" ;
    euai:contentOffset 209532 ;
    euai:fileName "EUAIAct-1-44.pdf" ;
    euai:pageNumber 30 ;
    euai:position 424 .

euai_c:af53860e3af32c7355b1dee7915dc8a8e4160fb8 a euai:DocumentChunk ;
    euai:chunkOf <https://euaiact.eu/resource/Document/EUAIAct-1-44_pdf> ;
    euai:chunkText " AI system  that transforms unstructured data into structured data, an AI system that classifies incoming documents into  categories or an AI system that is used to detect duplicates among a large number of applications. Those tasks are of  such narrow and limited nature that they pose only limited risks which are not increased through the use of an AI  system in a context that is listed as a high-risk use in an annex to this Regulation. The second condition should be  EN OJ L," ;
    euai:contentOffset 94901 ;
    euai:fileName "EUAIAct-1-44.pdf" ;
    euai:pageNumber 14 ;
    euai:position 198 .

euai_c:b689721ed569d025cfe605907260aba18dca8235 a euai:DocumentChunk ;
    euai:chunkOf <https://euaiact.eu/resource/Document/EUAIAct-1-44_pdf> ;
    euai:chunkText ") Regulation (EU) 2022/2065 of the European Parliament and of the Council of 19 October 2022 on a Single Market For Digital  Services and amending Directive 2000/31/EC (Digital Services Act) (OJ L 277, 27.10.2022, p. 1)." ;
    euai:contentOffset 25926 ;
    euai:fileName "EUAIAct-1-44.pdf" ;
    euai:pageNumber 4 ;
    euai:position 56 .

euai_c:e9985e6bcbccf5476c0cb6e61ad038e4e730f85a a euai:DocumentChunk ;
    euai:chunkOf <https://euaiact.eu/resource/Document/EUAIAct-1-44_pdf> ;
    euai:chunkText "Regulation should apply. For example, Article 16(2) of Regulation (EU) 2017/745, establishing that certain changes  should not be considered to be modifications of a device that could affect its compliance with the applicable  requirements, should continue to apply to high-risk AI systems that are medical devices within the meaning of that  Regulation. (85) General-purpose AI systems may be used as high-risk AI systems by themselves or be components of other high-risk  AI systems" ;
    euai:contentOffset 162282 ;
    euai:fileName "EUAIAct-1-44.pdf" ;
    euai:pageNumber 24 ;
    euai:position 331 .

