    euai:chunkText " unless they are used for identifying or inferring emotions. Those expressions can be basic  facial expressions, such as a frown or a smile, or gestures such as the movement of hands, arms or head, or  characteristics of a person’s voice, such as a raised voice or whispering. (19) For the purposes of this Regulation the notion of ‘publicly accessible space’ should be understood as referring to any  physical space that is accessible to an undetermined number of natural" ;
