    euai:chunkText "  that end, appropriate human oversight measures should be identified by the provider of the system before its placing  on the market or putting into service. In particular, where appropriate, such measures should guarantee that the  system is subject to in-built operational constraints that cannot be overridden by the system itself and is responsive  to the human operator, and that the natural persons to whom human oversight has been assigned have the necessary  competence, training and authority to carry out that role. It is also essential" ;
